        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>Novr 3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 1852</date>&#44;</p>
			<p>My Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">As it so seldom<lb/> falls to my lot&#44; to have the plea&#45;<lb/>sure of hearing from you&#44; I am<lb/> rather tardy in applying for<lb/> letters&#59; but there is an old adage<lb/> and a trite one &#8220;Better late than<lb/> never.&#8221;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I use all endeavors<lb/> to circulate your &#8220;Occident&#8221; but<lb/> with little success&#44; they would<lb/> here willingly read them gratis&#44;<lb/> but I do not encourage such a<lb/> mean system. I have but two<lb/> subscribers. <persName>Mr. Phs. Bravo</persName><lb/> and <persName>Mr. Harris</persName> both of them you<lb/> may <sic>advertize</sic> as paid from<lb/> <date>April</date>&#44; the amount as you advised<lb/> me to be handed over to <persName>Miss<lb/> Peixotto</persName> say 28&#47; I <sic>dont</sic> know<lb/> how your accounts stand with<lb/> each other so I am unable to<lb/> make any limits.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">A bible was once<lb/> ordered for one <persName>Revrd Duncan Campbell</persName><lb/> were you send two or three</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>for approval&#44; the frequent commu&#45;<lb/>nication I have with the Christian<lb/> clergy might enable me to dispose<lb/> of them.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The books I wish could <lb/>be sent immediately as I require<lb/> them&#44; let me know the amt &#38;<lb/> I can remit it for you&#44; the following also have been ordered<lb/> <persName>Dr. Wise&#39;s</persName> work&#8212;3 copies<lb/> <persName>Dr Illowy</persName> on the origin and<lb/> reasons of the Jewish Ceremonies&#8221;<lb/>&#8212;if completed&#8212;3 copies</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Could you be kind enough<lb/> also at the request of <persName>Miss Peixotto</persName><lb/> to send say a couple of dozen<lb/> of her Catechisms for this market<lb/> you would oblige.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I am so busy or would<lb/> gladly contribute to your periodical<lb/> in a literary way but I shall<lb/> endeavor to muster sufficient<lb/> time next opportunity.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Poor <persName>D. Garfaty&#39;s</persName> death<lb/> shocked us all and you may<lb/> judge the state of his family on<lb/> the receipt of such lamentable news</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">nothing further to add</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I subscribe myself</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Ever Thine</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">A Dehevanto</persName></p>
          
        </body>
